Array: it is collection similar/homogeneous data type values stored in a variable.

1. arrays works based index concepts

2. array index starts from zero(0),
   ends with length/size-1

Types of Arrays:

1. one dimensional array
		- how to declare and initialize one dimensional array.

=> one dimensional array declare and initialize in one statement/line	

for example, int customerAges[] = {29, 56, 33};

=> one dimensional array declare and initialize in multiple statements/lines
		
2. multidimensional array
		- how to declare and initialize multidimensional array.
		
=> multidimensional array declare and initialize in one statement/line	

for example, int matrix[][] = {{29, 56},{90 33}};

=> multidimensional array declare and initialize in multiple statements/lines

for example, int matrix[][] = new int[2][2];

			 matrix[0][0] = 1;
			 matrix[0][1] = 0;
			 matrix[1][0] = 1;
			 matrix[1][1] = 0;
			 
